        "@type": "FAQPage",
        "mainEntity": [
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "When is the best time to sell in Oxley?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "Autumn (March to May) and spring (September to November) are the most active periods for Oxley's buyer mix of first home buyers, investors and families. First home buyer activity is somewhat rate-sensitive, so periods of stable interest rates tend to strengthen results regardless of season. Avoid December and January, when overall buyer activity compresses around school holidays."
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "How long does it take to sell a house in Oxley?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "Well-presented Oxley homes typically sell within 28 to 45 days. Properties within easy walking distance of Oxley Station at the right price sell at the faster end. Those on busier roads or with larger renovation requirements take longer as the buyer pool is more selective."
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What is my Oxley home worth in 2026?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "Oxley values are driven by rail access and station proximity, block size, renovation condition and position relative to Oxley Creek. The gap between a well-presented, station-adjacent home and an unrenovated property further from transport is meaningful. Contact Daniel for a precise current appraisal of your specific property."
            }
          }
        ]
      }
      </script>

